manumit
	v. release from slavery; set free
nascent
	adj. (process of an org) just coming into existence and beginning to display signs of future potential
turpitude
	n. depravity; wickedness
buttressed
	n. a projecting support of stone or brick built against a wall
polemical
	adj. relating to or involving strongly critical, controversial, or disputatious writing or speech
sangfroid
	n. composure or coolness, sometimes excessive, as shown in danger or under trying circumstances
adroit
	adj. clever or skillful in using the hands or mind
assuaging
	v. make (and unpleasant feeling) less intense
disinclination
	n. a reluctance or lack of enthusiasm
jurisprudence
	n. the theory or philosophy of law
rejoinder
	n. a reply, especially a sharp or witty one
incongruous
	adj. not in harmony or keeping with the surroundings or other aspects of something
contrite
	adj. feeling or expressing remorse or penitence; affected by guilt
loquacious
	adj. tending to talk a great deal